    "shortDescription": "<p>A touched creature becomes invisible (as per invisibility) as long as it is in direct sunlight (or bright light shed by a <i>daylight</i> spell). If an action the target creature takes causes the invisible creature to become visible but does not end the <i>sunstalker</i> spell's duration, the creature can use this spell's magic to become invisible again as a standard action as long as it stands in an area of sunlight (as defined above). The creature gains only concealment (20% miss chance) in normal light.</p>"
